    "body": "@alexandraB99 I think allowing users to send empty messages compromise the user experience for other users. It's a more dangerous spam opportunity than just writing random text - it may make the channel / chat look broken - like the messages are not loading properly.  I can't think of a constructive use for allowing the user to send empty messages. Perhaps we remove the ability to send an empty message for now, aligning with other messaging apps. If there is a use case we discover later down the line we can assess the legitimacy of that use case and weigh up the benefit against the cost in experience to other users. ",
